The paper focuses on the development of a force estimation model for Robot-Assisted Minimally Invasive Surgery systems, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The proposed model is based on Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and Long-Short Term Memory (LSTM) networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The paper also discusses the challenges of processing spatiotemporal information and the need for a loss function, which are relevant topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY).
